Section 2. The seat of the government of the Municipality of General Mariano Alvarez shall be at the present site of the Barangay of San Gabriel.1awp++i1
Section 3. Except as hereafter provided, all laws, now or hereafter applicable to regular municipalities, shall be applicable to the Municipality of General Mariano Alvarez.
Section 4. The Municipality of General Mariano Alvarez shall become existent upon the ratification by majority of the votes cast in a plebiscite to be conducted in the municipality of Carmona and the new Municipality of General Mariano Alvarez within a period of one hundred eighty days after the approval of this Act, after which the President of the Philippines (Prime Minister) shall appoint the first mayor, vice mayor, other municipal officials and barangay officials of the said municipality as provided for under existing laws.
The Commission on Elections shall conduct and supervise the plebiscite. The expenses for such plebiscite shall be paid out of the appropriations provided under the General Appropriations Act for the Commission on Elections.
Section 5. Upon the effectivity of this Act, the proportionate share of the Municipality of General Mariano Alvarez in the obligations, funds, assets and other properties of the Municipality of Carmona shall be transferred by the President of the Philippines (Prime Minister) to the newly created municipality upon the recommendation of the Commission on Audit.
Section 6. All laws or parts of laws as well as executive orders or regulations inconsistent herewith are hereby repealed or modified accordingly.
Section 7. This Act shall take effect upon its approval.
Approved: June 13, 1980

